<br>
IRL, I abhor racism. I am utterly disgusted by it. However, EQ is not RL. EQ is a fantasy medieval world in which there are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>supposed</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to be racial tensions and conflicts. In real life, we don't have races that are supposed to be evilly aligned, correct? <br>
<br>
Duplicitas does a great deal of things that do not appeal to me in real life. For instance, she has no interest in finding a mate, but she still has urges. She sleeps with prostitutes to avoid making an emotional connection to anyone. She won't allow anyone to have that sort of advantage over her. <br>
<br>
In real life, I can assure you that I don't go around picking up prostitutes, nor would I ever consider doing so. I am playing a character. I am acting a part in an online play. I find evil characters in movies interesting, usually more interesting than the hero. We all understand the hero's motivations, but there's something intriguing about the evil character, because I don't know exactly where they're coming from. There's more mystery surrounding them, and that's why I decided to play an evil character myself. I wanted to see if I could play her believably, and in playing her as a racist who does questionable things and lives by her own code of honour and morality, that's what I'm trying to do. She wouldn't be very convincing if she walked around holding hands with my Paladin, would she?<br>
<br>
My Paladin is a light reflection of Duplicitas. She is virtuous and pure, happily married to a Fier`Dal Druid, and yet, she is racist too. She will cheerfully kill anything of evil race or class. Even those annoying little &quot;good&quot; Teir`Dal. She doesn't care that you repented. You're the creation of an evil God, and that's enough for her.<br>
<br>
So, I play the purest good and the darkest evil. I enjoy playing as both of my characters a good deal, but that doesn't mean I carry the same attitudes as they do in the real world. <br>
<br>
