<br>
Has it occured to you people that faction = racism??<br>
  <br>
If there was not racial tensions then we would just RP that we all hate the monsters? ...oh wait that makes us monster bigots...we better just hunt animals?...oh wait that makes us animal bogots.<br>
<br>
Simply put you cannot equate real life with roleplay, that is moronic.  The goals are so contrary that they cannot possibly share the same morals or ethics concerning racial tensions.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">In real life the goal is peace, we prosper when we have no conflict.</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">In fantasy roleplay (EQ, D&amp;D..etc...) we <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>only</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> prosper through conflict</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.  <br>
<br>
In Everquest we have to kill to grow strong, if you kill what another race of people like...you create what?<br>
<br>
RACIAL TENSIONS<br>
<br>
Not to mention if you kill the people themselves.  A good example on the continent of Velious...the entire freaking expansion revolves around racial tensions.<br>
<br>
So please...please...PLEASE people, give me a fucking break from your mouth running about how playing a racist in a game built around racial tensions is somehow wrong or makes me untrustworthy. ~rolls eyes~<br>
<br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
<br>
I think the core of the problem is that most people, even those who refer to themselves as old school or hardcore RPers don't have a clue what RP really is.<br>
<br>
RP is not you creating a character in an environment and playing as if it is you yourself in that environment.  That is just fantasy.<br>
<br>
Roleplaying is you creating an individual that is different from yourself and behaving as they would...not as you would.<br>
<br>
<br>
This is why I RP evil, if I played a heroic type character it would just be be fantasizing about how I would be given the abilities and environment.  As an evil I can actually walk in a different individuals shoes.<br>
<br>
I guess I could just say that RPing is not pretending your some<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>where</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> else, it is pretending that you are some<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>body</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> else.<br>
<br>
<br>
I don't know, I have a feeling I could explain it a thousand different ways and people just won't be able to see it, or perhaps won't be willing to.<br>
<br>
~goes back to his trolling~<br>
<br>
<br>
